evidence to the contrary, is proof of the matters stated in the
certificate:
         (a)     the person named in the certificate is liable to pay tax;
         (b)     an assessment of tax has been made in relation to circumstances
specified in the certificate;
         (c)     notice of an assessment was issued to a person named in the
certificate, or the person's agent, on the day specified in the
certificate;
         (d)     the amount of tax, penalty tax or interest specified in the
certificate is payable by a person named in the certificate or has been paid in
whole or in part by or on behalf of a person so named;
         (e)     a document specified in the certificate was posted to, delivered to,
or served personally on, a person named in the certificate on a day specified in
the certificate;
         (f)     a person named in the certificate is, or is not, registered or
licensed as required by the relevant tax law;
         (g)     a return or statement required by a tax law has been, or has not been,
lodged by or on behalf of a person named in the certificate on or as at a day
specified in the certificate;
         (h)     a person named in the certificate is, or was, an authorised officer on
the date specified in the certificate.

"scheme" means the following:
         (a)     a deferral scheme;
         (b)     an exemption scheme;
         (c)     a rebate scheme.
